1
00:00:05,801 --> 00:00:07,331
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:07,401 --> 00:00:09,171
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:10,301 --> 00:00:12,341
(Episode 38)

4
00:00:12,401 --> 00:00:14,371
(Taehan Group)

5
00:00:16,941 --> 00:00:18,041
Mr. Park Jun Hyeok.

6
00:00:28,751 --> 00:00:31,351
I'm honored you know my name,
Director Baek.

7
00:00:31,951 --> 00:00:34,761
How could I not?
You're key to the Fashion Division.

8
00:00:35,891 --> 00:00:39,061
Thank you for your great interest
in our Fashion Division.

9
00:00:39,061 --> 00:00:40,401
We're truly grateful.

10
00:00:44,201 --> 00:00:46,671
I hear you're close with the VP
and Director Yang.

11
00:00:47,201 --> 00:00:48,911
You and I should get close as well.

12
00:00:50,511 --> 00:00:52,111
You want me to do what?

13
00:00:53,211 --> 00:00:54,281
Go undercover.

14
00:00:55,411 --> 00:00:57,381
Under what?

15
00:00:58,051 --> 00:01:00,751
Undercover. Undercover Mr. Park.

16
00:01:03,151 --> 00:01:04,151
I like the sound of that.

17
00:01:04,351 --> 00:01:07,661
If Director Baek is dead set
on taking down the Fashion Division,

18
00:01:08,121 --> 00:01:09,591
to get information on us,

19
00:01:09,931 --> 00:01:11,961
you'll be the first person
he approaches.

20
00:01:13,501 --> 00:01:15,931
- Why me?
- You're the most connected here.

21
00:01:16,231 --> 00:01:17,631
And you have a big mouth.

22
00:01:20,471 --> 00:01:21,971
That sounds like an insult.

23
00:01:22,411 --> 00:01:23,741
It means you're perfect for the job.

24
00:01:25,741 --> 00:01:27,881
What do you need me to do?

25
00:01:30,981 --> 00:01:32,751
And what's that supposed to mean?

26
00:01:32,921 --> 00:01:37,091
A flatterer, a suck-up,
a yes-man, a sycophant.

27
00:01:38,651 --> 00:01:39,761
Roger that.

28
00:01:40,591 --> 00:01:43,061
I hear you're close with the VP
and Director Yang.

29
00:01:43,691 --> 00:01:45,461
You and I should get close as well.

30
00:01:45,761 --> 00:01:47,401
Of course, Director Baek.
It would be my honor.

31
00:01:47,661 --> 00:01:49,671
Perhaps we could grab
a coffee sometime?

32
00:01:52,601 --> 00:01:54,001
Sure, why not?

33
00:01:55,001 --> 00:01:56,041
Great.

34
00:01:56,041 --> 00:01:59,711
You must find out
what Director Baek's true goal is.

35
00:02:17,531 --> 00:02:19,461
What's with the cocky attitude?

36
00:02:20,531 --> 00:02:23,671
Just because you have
the top executives in your pocket,

37
00:02:24,001 --> 00:02:25,401
you think you're untouchable?

38
00:02:27,901 --> 00:02:31,341
You look like you want to punch me.
Always so authoritarian.

39
00:02:32,711 --> 00:02:34,241
How did it go?

40
00:02:34,881 --> 00:02:36,011
It was way too easy.

41
00:02:36,281 --> 00:02:40,421
At this rate, the great Taehan
might actually fall into my hands.

42
00:02:41,621 --> 00:02:43,051
I have to admit, you're good.

43
00:02:44,051 --> 00:02:47,121
You said it was just tea,
but you even stayed for dinner.

44
00:02:47,961 --> 00:02:50,131
I had some incredible sashimi
for the first time in ages.

45
00:02:50,561 --> 00:02:51,731
And that's not all.

46
00:02:52,401 --> 00:02:54,931
I'm going golfing
with the other executives.

47
00:02:56,501 --> 00:02:57,501
You are?

48
00:02:58,371 --> 00:03:01,641
What can I say?
That's the Park Jun Hyeok charm.

49
00:03:03,571 --> 00:03:06,381
He's bold and good-looking.

50
00:03:06,881 --> 00:03:08,011
And he's a smooth talker.

51
00:03:09,481 --> 00:03:11,911
He'd make a better figurehead
than the Vice President.

52
00:03:12,421 --> 00:03:13,421
Yes, sir.

53
00:03:13,751 --> 00:03:15,691
- What about the paternity test?
- Oh, that.

54
00:03:16,221 --> 00:03:19,961
I got the utensils and glass he used
after dinner and sent them out.

55
00:03:20,821 --> 00:03:23,761
He'll be useful
even if he's not the Chairman's son.

56
00:03:24,091 --> 00:03:26,661
He's also perfect
for feeding them false information.

57
00:03:27,231 --> 00:03:28,231
Right, sir.

58
00:03:32,201 --> 00:03:35,571
He said he'll stop interfering
and will help the Fashion Division.

59
00:03:37,271 --> 00:03:40,111
If he can't get rid of it,
he might as well build it up.

60
00:03:40,111 --> 00:03:41,181
I think that's what he's thinking.

61
00:03:41,711 --> 00:03:44,911
Tell him I was thrilled
to hear the news.

62
00:03:45,821 --> 00:03:46,821
Got it.

63
00:03:48,351 --> 00:03:50,021
By the way, I heard something
on my way over.

64
00:03:50,451 --> 00:03:52,121
I heard things got wild today.

65
00:03:52,761 --> 00:03:53,821
Wild how?

66
00:03:54,161 --> 00:03:56,861
Your mother and Ju Ah,

67
00:03:57,131 --> 00:03:59,231
and then your mother and you,

68
00:03:59,861 --> 00:04:01,431
had a double-header of a fight.

69
00:04:03,571 --> 00:04:04,601
So we did.

70
00:04:05,501 --> 00:04:08,871
Ju Ah has a really tough time
with your mother.

71
00:04:09,811 --> 00:04:10,841
I know.

72
00:04:11,541 --> 00:04:15,881
Your mother
is a pretty intense mother-in-law.

73
00:04:17,281 --> 00:04:18,311
I know.

74
00:04:18,911 --> 00:04:21,921
I'm telling you, being an orphan
is a major selling point with women.

75
00:04:23,191 --> 00:04:24,391
Am I supposed to be envious?

76
00:04:27,291 --> 00:04:30,861
What are you going to do?
Aren't you going to see Ju Ah again?

77
00:04:31,831 --> 00:04:33,761
I'm not sure that's an option.

78
00:04:34,061 --> 00:04:37,031
Because soon,
we're about to become a family.

79
00:04:37,431 --> 00:04:38,531
A family?

80
00:04:39,341 --> 00:04:40,841
Who is? With whom?

81
00:04:47,841 --> 00:04:52,081
- This is quite good.
- Yes, you picked a great spot.

82
00:04:52,381 --> 00:04:53,381
Yes.

83
00:04:54,951 --> 00:04:57,191
But what's taking them so long?

84
00:04:58,491 --> 00:05:01,191
Did Ju Ah go with them?
Why isn't she back yet?

85
00:05:01,491 --> 00:05:03,431
Ju Ah left before them.

86
00:05:04,091 --> 00:05:07,031
I'm sure she'll be here soon.
Please, eat.

87
00:05:07,861 --> 00:05:09,501
- Let's eat.
- All right.

88
00:05:10,871 --> 00:05:11,871
Counseling?

89
00:05:12,801 --> 00:05:16,211
So I suppose when psychiatrists talk
to another's husband day and night,

90
00:05:16,271 --> 00:05:18,741
do they call private phone calls
"counseling?"

91
00:05:19,011 --> 00:05:21,641
- What did you say?
- Using your profession...

92
00:05:21,811 --> 00:05:23,581
as an excuse to dig into
other people's private lives.

93
00:05:23,581 --> 00:05:24,751
Did you have fun?

94
00:05:25,051 --> 00:05:27,951
I was just giving some advice
to an emotionally drained friend,

95
00:05:28,281 --> 00:05:29,751
and you twist it into
something like this.

96
00:05:30,121 --> 00:05:33,021
It's a pity your understanding
is so shallow.

97
00:05:34,291 --> 00:05:36,391
- So pretentious.
- What did you say?

98
00:05:36,461 --> 00:05:40,001
Forget it. Why am I wasting my time
arguing with a patient?

99
00:05:41,001 --> 00:05:42,871
Excuse me? Seriously?

100
00:05:42,871 --> 00:05:45,731
Seriously, I can't
take this anymore.

101
00:05:46,671 --> 00:05:47,701
(Occupied, Vacant)

102
00:05:50,641 --> 00:05:52,071
You think you can say
whatever you want?

103
00:06:06,061 --> 00:06:07,821
Ju Ah, let's just go. Okay?

104
00:06:08,191 --> 00:06:10,931
I'm not going anywhere.
I have to say what needs to be said.

105
00:06:13,131 --> 00:06:14,131
What?

106
00:06:18,001 --> 00:06:19,501
I said let's go.

107
00:06:22,841 --> 00:06:23,971
What do you have to say?

108
00:06:26,041 --> 00:06:27,211
If you have something to say,
say it.

109
00:06:30,481 --> 00:06:32,211
Seriously, what's wrong with you?

110
00:06:32,951 --> 00:06:34,051
Go on. I'm waiting.

111
00:06:35,121 --> 00:06:38,091
For a patient to discuss
their spouse with a psychiatrist...

112
00:06:38,151 --> 00:06:41,691
- is perfectly normal.
- This wasn't an official session.

113
00:06:41,991 --> 00:06:44,261
I'm saying it's because
she had ulterior motives.

114
00:06:44,931 --> 00:06:45,961
Ulterior motives?

115
00:06:46,531 --> 00:06:47,531
Am I wrong?

116
00:06:47,831 --> 00:06:48,831
Watch what you say.

117
00:06:52,271 --> 00:06:53,271
Let's just stop this.

118
00:06:53,701 --> 00:06:56,571
Why? Did I strike a nerve?

119
00:06:57,241 --> 00:06:59,911
Your separation stems
directly from your own relationship.

120
00:07:00,181 --> 00:07:02,611
My mom is not the reason
you two are separated.

121
00:07:03,411 --> 00:07:06,151
I'm well aware
you're jealous of my mother.

122
00:07:06,281 --> 00:07:07,621
But this habit
of constantly trying...

123
00:07:07,621 --> 00:07:08,981
to frame my mom
as the other woman...

124
00:07:09,291 --> 00:07:11,251
is a textbook case
of psychological projection.

125
00:07:13,021 --> 00:07:14,291
What, are you a doctor or something?

126
00:07:14,421 --> 00:07:17,931
Yes. I went to med school,
and I have my license.

127
00:07:19,301 --> 00:07:20,301
I see.

128
00:07:20,631 --> 00:07:23,571
You're not upset because
people found out you're separated.

129
00:07:24,131 --> 00:07:26,671
You're upset that he came to me
for help, aren't you?

130
00:07:27,371 --> 00:07:29,471
- I understand.
- If you understood,

131
00:07:30,311 --> 00:07:31,911
you should have been more careful.

132
00:07:33,941 --> 00:07:35,041
I said I understand.

133
00:07:36,751 --> 00:07:38,051
Let's just drop it and go, okay?

134
00:07:39,181 --> 00:07:41,321
I know you've spent
your whole life working,

135
00:07:41,881 --> 00:07:45,721
and being a patient
has hurt your pride,

136
00:07:45,751 --> 00:07:47,591
so you seek comfort
by doting on my husband.

137
00:07:48,161 --> 00:07:49,391
But from now on,

138
00:07:49,861 --> 00:07:52,731
I'd appreciate it if you'd avoid
any behavior that could be misread.

139
00:07:54,231 --> 00:07:56,331
Mocking someone
for being sick like that.

140
00:07:56,401 --> 00:07:58,971
Do you realize
how despicable and crass that is?

141
00:07:59,241 --> 00:08:00,301
Mocking?

142
00:08:00,771 --> 00:08:04,011
What's so offensive about
calling a patient a patient?

143
00:08:05,841 --> 00:08:08,211
If you don't find that offensive,
then I have something to say too.

144
00:08:08,741 --> 00:08:12,151
My mother's not the only patient,
so is Director Yang's.

145
00:08:13,181 --> 00:08:17,721
As a doctor, I suspect you have
pathological jealousy and delusions.

146
00:08:18,521 --> 00:08:21,161
Stop it, Ju Ah.
What's gotten into you today?

147
00:08:22,061 --> 00:08:23,091
Go.

148
00:08:23,591 --> 00:08:24,661
Let's just go.

149
00:08:27,601 --> 00:08:28,801
The nerve of her.

150
00:08:34,341 --> 00:08:35,501
Honey.

151
00:08:36,811 --> 00:08:38,311
What took you so long?

152
00:08:40,511 --> 00:08:41,681
Where have you been?

153
00:08:45,281 --> 00:08:47,051
About the wedding...

154
00:08:47,681 --> 00:08:49,591
Even if they have it
after they find Gi Cheol,

155
00:08:49,891 --> 00:08:53,791
shouldn't they make it official
and move in together first?

156
00:08:54,191 --> 00:08:57,361
Yes, I agree. At their age,

157
00:08:57,431 --> 00:08:59,931
why waste time?

158
00:09:00,761 --> 00:09:03,271
- Right, Dae Han?
- Yes.

159
00:09:04,601 --> 00:09:09,311
Then do you have any ideas
about where they should live?

160
00:09:11,171 --> 00:09:16,451
What I'd really like is
for Dong Suk to come live with us.

161
00:09:17,151 --> 00:09:20,721
My heart aches for her,
having grown up without a mother.

162
00:09:21,181 --> 00:09:26,691
So now I'd like to step in
for In Ok and look after her.

163
00:09:26,961 --> 00:09:29,191
That's very generous of you.
Thank you.

164
00:09:30,591 --> 00:09:32,931
But still...

165
00:09:32,931 --> 00:09:34,331
To be honest,

166
00:09:35,131 --> 00:09:38,201
moving in with the in-laws
right away is a bit much.

167
00:09:39,401 --> 00:09:40,871
Since Dr. Han's sick,

168
00:09:40,871 --> 00:09:43,211
who knows Dong Suk
might end up caring for her?

169
00:09:45,111 --> 00:09:46,111
Oh my, Se Ri.

170
00:09:46,111 --> 00:09:49,281
Besides, if my Ji Hu moves in too,
he'll be walking on eggshells,

171
00:09:49,481 --> 00:09:52,151
and I'm worried
he'll just feel like a burden.

172
00:09:52,651 --> 00:09:56,151
Besides, the house is small.
You don't even have a spare room.

173
00:09:56,751 --> 00:09:58,421
- Honey!
- What?

174
00:09:58,421 --> 00:10:01,061
Now that Dong Suk's mother
has passed away,

175
00:10:01,161 --> 00:10:03,161
I'm the one who has to
speak up for her.

176
00:10:03,831 --> 00:10:07,331
Look, if money is the problem,

177
00:10:07,531 --> 00:10:12,201
- we'll find them a place ourselves.
- Se Ri.

178
00:10:13,041 --> 00:10:16,941
Every single word you say
really says it all.

179
00:10:17,811 --> 00:10:19,711
- What?
- Ju Ah.

180
00:10:20,681 --> 00:10:24,211
- Says a lot about your parenting.
- Excuse me!

181
00:10:24,281 --> 00:10:27,921
Am I wrong?
How dare she be so rude to an elder.

182
00:10:28,721 --> 00:10:32,761
- Then act like an adult.
- What?

183
00:10:32,821 --> 00:10:36,391
You're just taking
your anger out on my mom...

184
00:10:36,491 --> 00:10:41,101
- from your own therapy?
- Wait, how did you know?

185
00:10:41,631 --> 00:10:45,601
So all this time,
just because I'm Hyun Bin's mother,

186
00:10:45,671 --> 00:10:47,841
you've been hiding
how you really feel?

187
00:10:48,201 --> 00:10:51,041
So now that you've broken up,
you can just say whatever you want?

188
00:10:53,081 --> 00:10:55,981
Wait, what?
What is she talking about?

189
00:10:56,681 --> 00:11:00,581
Ju Ah. Is that true?

190
00:11:02,021 --> 00:11:03,991
Yes. It seems so.

191
00:11:04,491 --> 00:11:07,861
I liked Yang Hyun Bin, and we dated.

192
00:11:11,691 --> 00:11:15,631
I was so blinded by love,
so head over heels,

193
00:11:15,831 --> 00:11:19,001
that however awfully you behaved,
I put up with it,

194
00:11:19,471 --> 00:11:22,141
and I guess I just hid it
from my family.

195
00:11:23,671 --> 00:11:25,511
"How awfully I behaved?"

196
00:11:26,211 --> 00:11:27,881
What did I do that was so awful?

197
00:11:29,011 --> 00:11:31,911
Have you forgotten?
Should I list them all out for you?

198
00:11:32,511 --> 00:11:35,951
- Ju Ah, please.
- You used my mom's photo...

199
00:11:36,021 --> 00:11:39,921
and spread rumors of an affair.
You also hit and injured her eye.

200
00:11:48,201 --> 00:11:50,631
I didn't hit her on purpose,
you know.

201
00:11:51,431 --> 00:11:53,901
Then what about during
the One-Point Lesson?

202
00:11:53,971 --> 00:11:56,541
You posted that video of yourself
falling on purpose, didn't you?

203
00:11:57,041 --> 00:11:59,041
(Gong Ju Ah, Lead Designer,
Taehan Group)

204
00:11:59,111 --> 00:12:00,881
You made sure I was disciplined,

205
00:12:01,211 --> 00:12:04,081
and then you deliberately pretended
to save me.

206
00:12:04,151 --> 00:12:05,951
I thought it would be better
to tell you in person.

207
00:12:06,351 --> 00:12:09,951
To get back at me for
my "awful behavior,"

208
00:12:10,991 --> 00:12:13,861
you used my son and had him
clean up all your messes,

209
00:12:13,921 --> 00:12:16,331
and then had your family reject him
so he'd want to leave the country?

210
00:12:16,431 --> 00:12:18,731
No, the reason
we were against it was...

211
00:12:18,791 --> 00:12:23,101
Director Yang is staying in Korea
for his family's sake.

212
00:12:23,631 --> 00:12:26,801
I resigned so that
we'd never see each other again.

213
00:12:27,141 --> 00:12:28,371
Are you satisfied now?

214
00:12:32,711 --> 00:12:34,711
- Honey!
- Oh, my stomach.

215
00:12:34,741 --> 00:12:35,741
Mom, are you okay?

216
00:12:36,181 --> 00:12:38,151
Ju Ah, help your mom.

217
00:12:39,251 --> 00:12:43,651
It's nothing, really. Please, ma'am,
don't get up. Ju Ah.

218
00:12:43,721 --> 00:12:47,191
- Oh, careful, careful, careful.
- Does it hurt a lot?

219
00:12:48,791 --> 00:12:50,261
Oh, good grief.

220
00:12:57,301 --> 00:12:58,431
Hyun Bin...

221
00:12:59,131 --> 00:13:01,671
and Ju Ah were dating, it seems?

222
00:13:02,001 --> 00:13:03,011
Yes.

223
00:13:04,171 --> 00:13:07,111
It's true. I was the one
who was against it, sir.

224
00:13:07,411 --> 00:13:08,641
Of course. That's only natural.

225
00:13:10,011 --> 00:13:11,981
Things were different back then,
weren't they?

226
00:13:14,421 --> 00:13:17,751
A few days ago,
when Dae Han came to my house,

227
00:13:18,091 --> 00:13:19,391
I slammed the door in his face.

228
00:13:19,661 --> 00:13:23,561
Father, Hyun Bin almost left
for Argentina!

229
00:13:23,631 --> 00:13:25,561
But she said he's not going!

230
00:13:26,761 --> 00:13:30,201
Why are you making a scene?
This is Dong Suk's fresh start.

231
00:13:30,401 --> 00:13:32,071
I'm not making a scene.

232
00:13:32,401 --> 00:13:35,801
- She's so rude and disrespectful.
- Se Ri!

233
00:13:36,541 --> 00:13:38,841
How long are you going to keep
embarrassing me?

234
00:13:39,141 --> 00:13:42,011
How much longer must I cover for you
and try to understand?

235
00:13:43,151 --> 00:13:44,311
Father...

236
00:13:46,581 --> 00:13:48,151
I'm sorry, Ms. Na.

237
00:14:09,841 --> 00:14:12,671
What a mess.

238
00:14:19,511 --> 00:14:20,981
Honey!

239
00:14:21,681 --> 00:14:22,751
Wait!

240
00:14:23,451 --> 00:14:26,121
Don't get so worked up.
Just calm down a little. Okay?

241
00:14:26,191 --> 00:14:29,091
How do you expect me to be calm?
How could you do this?

242
00:14:30,561 --> 00:14:34,231
I was publicly humiliated,
and you didn't even take my side?

243
00:14:34,431 --> 00:14:38,071
What, with all the elders there,
you wanted me to start fighting too?

244
00:14:38,531 --> 00:14:39,531
Come on, honey.

245
00:14:39,871 --> 00:14:43,671
Today's a big day for Dong Suk.
Right?

246
00:14:44,111 --> 00:14:45,371
How could you...

247
00:14:46,441 --> 00:14:48,581
not once think about how I feel?

248
00:14:49,211 --> 00:14:50,851
Hey, if I didn't care about you,

249
00:14:51,111 --> 00:14:53,121
why would I have gone to counseling?

250
00:14:54,251 --> 00:14:56,721
I thought my trauma...

251
00:14:56,921 --> 00:14:59,251
was ruining our relationship,

252
00:14:59,421 --> 00:15:01,991
so I'm doing
everything I can to fix it.

253
00:15:02,061 --> 00:15:05,931
How could you go
to Dr. Han Seong Mi?

254
00:15:06,061 --> 00:15:08,801
How could you get couples counseling
from her?

255
00:15:09,771 --> 00:15:14,201
Se Ri, Seong Mi is an expert
in family matters,

256
00:15:14,301 --> 00:15:17,271
- and a psychiatrist.
- Is that all? A psychiatrist?

257
00:15:17,871 --> 00:15:19,471
She's your first love!

258
00:15:20,511 --> 00:15:21,581
Gosh.

259
00:15:22,381 --> 00:15:25,651
Why bring that up now?

260
00:15:25,881 --> 00:15:29,181
You told me she was the first person
you ever truly loved.

261
00:15:29,721 --> 00:15:30,951
My entire life,

262
00:15:31,351 --> 00:15:34,591
I felt I was compared to her.
I always did.

263
00:15:35,561 --> 00:15:37,161
I felt I had to be better than her,

264
00:15:37,161 --> 00:15:38,731
and you have no idea
how hard it was.

265
00:15:38,891 --> 00:15:41,231
Don't cry, okay?
That was a long time ago.

266
00:15:41,801 --> 00:15:44,131
No, I'm sorry. It was my fault.

267
00:15:44,801 --> 00:15:48,341
What're you saying? You're the best.
There's no one else like you.

268
00:15:48,401 --> 00:15:51,211
You're way prettier
and smarter than Seong Mi.

269
00:15:51,941 --> 00:15:55,311
But you're the one
fixated on Seong Mi,

270
00:15:55,381 --> 00:15:57,651
and that's what's making
you so miserable.

271
00:15:58,151 --> 00:15:59,281
So,

272
00:16:00,581 --> 00:16:02,151
what was her "solution?"

273
00:16:03,151 --> 00:16:04,591
Did she tell you to divorce me
or something?

274
00:16:04,951 --> 00:16:06,991
- Se Ri.
- Dong Ik.

275
00:16:07,661 --> 00:16:10,261
Do you know how much Hyun Bin
backed me into a corner today?

276
00:16:10,631 --> 00:16:13,931
You're not yourself today.
What's gotten into you?

277
00:16:14,501 --> 00:16:15,661
Look, let's think about this.

278
00:16:16,061 --> 00:16:18,631
He must have had it rough too,
right?

279
00:16:18,901 --> 00:16:20,371
They were dating,

280
00:16:20,501 --> 00:16:24,971
- but their families broke them up.
- That's right.

281
00:16:26,111 --> 00:16:27,581
They said it's my fault
they broke up.

282
00:16:27,881 --> 00:16:29,811
It's all my fault. So,

283
00:16:30,911 --> 00:16:33,951
- I'd be better off gone.
- What? No, that's not it.

284
00:16:34,321 --> 00:16:35,381
Se Ri.

285
00:16:39,291 --> 00:16:40,761
What am I supposed to do?

286
00:17:03,951 --> 00:17:08,151
Gosh, what a disaster.
Seriously. Hey, are you okay?

287
00:17:08,821 --> 00:17:09,821
I'm fine.

288
00:17:10,521 --> 00:17:12,891
I just left so Ju Ah wouldn't
cause a bigger scene.

289
00:17:13,591 --> 00:17:15,091
I figured as much.

290
00:17:15,721 --> 00:17:19,731
- Ju Ah really is something else.
- Let her be.

291
00:17:20,701 --> 00:17:22,261
To be honest, I'm relieved.

292
00:17:23,501 --> 00:17:25,131
Honestly, me too.

293
00:17:27,841 --> 00:17:31,471
But Ju Ah is clearly
your daughter, isn't she?

294
00:17:31,611 --> 00:17:34,911
When she gets angry,
she just goes nuclear.

295
00:17:34,981 --> 00:17:36,181
I swear.

296
00:17:38,281 --> 00:17:41,221
So, did Ju Ah...

297
00:17:41,281 --> 00:17:43,351
really go out with Bucket's son?

298
00:17:43,651 --> 00:17:47,091
They did, but they broke up.
Afraid their families would freak.

299
00:17:47,721 --> 00:17:50,661
I knew it. They were together a lot,
I had a feeling.

300
00:17:51,031 --> 00:17:53,501
It's in the past now.
Just act like you don't know.

301
00:17:54,461 --> 00:17:58,871
Anyway, Dong Ik's wife
seemed pissed off, didn't she?

302
00:17:59,601 --> 00:18:00,741
Tell me about it.

303
00:18:01,101 --> 00:18:04,371
That her husband confided in me
about their marriage...

304
00:18:04,541 --> 00:18:06,811
must have been a huge blow to her.

305
00:18:07,241 --> 00:18:10,181
It's like something happened
that was beyond her control.

306
00:18:10,911 --> 00:18:15,221
That makes sense
since Bucket had a crush on you.

307
00:18:15,551 --> 00:18:19,521
This is so unfair.
Is it my fault he had a crush on me?

308
00:18:20,091 --> 00:18:23,231
- A crush? Was it really one-sided?
- What?

309
00:18:23,291 --> 00:18:27,531
He's always giving me a hard time,
saying I stole you from him.

310
00:18:27,601 --> 00:18:30,401
Exactly, that's ridiculous.
It's not like I belonged to Bucket.

311
00:18:30,471 --> 00:18:31,471
What is there to steal?

312
00:18:31,731 --> 00:18:33,841
I know, right? Gosh, what a moron.

313
00:18:35,571 --> 00:18:37,911
For Dae Han's sake,
as he starts his new life,

314
00:18:38,241 --> 00:18:42,981
- we must sort this out for him.
- Okay, let's do it.

315
00:18:43,251 --> 00:18:46,951
At this rate,
Bucket's getting divorced again.

316
00:19:17,381 --> 00:19:21,051
What should have been a happy day
ended like this.

317
00:19:21,951 --> 00:19:25,491
Please forgive my granddaughter
for her rudeness.

318
00:19:26,051 --> 00:19:28,191
My daughter-in-law is
just as much to blame.

319
00:19:29,561 --> 00:19:30,661
I'm so sorry.

320
00:19:31,531 --> 00:19:32,531
It's all right.

321
00:19:34,061 --> 00:19:37,201
Mom, did you know
Ju Ah and Director Yang were dating?

322
00:19:38,901 --> 00:19:39,901
Yes.

323
00:19:41,601 --> 00:19:43,201
It seemed like a bad idea,

324
00:19:43,471 --> 00:19:45,241
so I stepped in
and put a stop to it.

325
00:19:46,311 --> 00:19:49,541
So that's what happened.
I'd seen them together,

326
00:19:50,251 --> 00:19:51,551
but I didn't realize
they were actually dating.

327
00:19:53,381 --> 00:19:54,621
Dong Suk, you knew about this?

328
00:19:55,251 --> 00:19:56,991
What? Yes.

329
00:19:57,851 --> 00:20:00,121
I only heard about it
after they'd broken up.

330
00:20:02,461 --> 00:20:04,291
Gosh, we were this close
to being double in-laws.

331
00:20:05,431 --> 00:20:07,661
- I know, right?
- That's ridiculous.

332
00:20:08,231 --> 00:20:11,601
Why not? Father,
it's not a big deal these days.

333
00:20:12,901 --> 00:20:15,671
Your nephew
and your husband's niece.

334
00:20:16,501 --> 00:20:17,811
How does that make any sense?

335
00:20:19,341 --> 00:20:20,341
Wouldn't you agree?

336
00:20:22,211 --> 00:20:25,111
- It would be complicated.
- It's out of the question.

337
00:21:01,651 --> 00:21:03,491
So it wasn't the moms.

338
00:21:03,551 --> 00:21:06,861
It was my mom and Gong Ju Ah
who had a showdown?

339
00:21:07,191 --> 00:21:10,691
It wasn't a showdown.
Your mom got completely knocked out.

340
00:21:11,261 --> 00:21:12,261
Oh my.

341
00:21:12,391 --> 00:21:16,931
I guess Gong Ju Ah has no intention
of getting back with you, Hyun Bin.

342
00:21:17,231 --> 00:21:22,101
I feel bad for my sister-in-law.
She's fighting Father and husband.

343
00:21:22,701 --> 00:21:23,711
It was just rough.

344
00:21:24,741 --> 00:21:27,881
She must be really upset.
No one's taking her side.

345
00:21:29,741 --> 00:21:31,751
Hey, why aren't you saying
a single word?

346
00:21:33,281 --> 00:21:34,551
What am I supposed to say?

347
00:21:34,951 --> 00:21:37,491
Put on a sympathetic face
and say something like,

348
00:21:38,851 --> 00:21:41,261
"I should go comfort Mom."

349
00:21:41,961 --> 00:21:46,091
Or, "Grandfather had a tough day.
I'll go check on him." Like that?

350
00:21:46,231 --> 00:21:47,401
And why should I?

351
00:21:47,931 --> 00:21:51,831
- What's with the sudden attitude?
- What attitude?

352
00:21:57,971 --> 00:21:58,971
Yes, Father.

353
00:21:59,611 --> 00:22:01,411
Okay. I'm coming down.

354
00:22:02,041 --> 00:22:05,081
Why are you calling me
when we're in the same house?

355
00:22:05,151 --> 00:22:07,051
You could've just yelled
for me to come down.

356
00:22:08,181 --> 00:22:09,181
Gosh!

357
00:22:11,491 --> 00:22:12,491
Oh, my.

358
00:22:12,921 --> 00:22:15,791
- What's gotten into him?
- Teenage angst, I guess.

359
00:22:16,961 --> 00:22:18,091
Feel better now?

360
00:22:19,661 --> 00:22:21,901
I was so out of line, Grandma.

361
00:22:23,671 --> 00:22:26,031
No, you did the right thing.

362
00:22:26,501 --> 00:22:27,501
What?

363
00:22:27,871 --> 00:22:29,471
After all the times
you've held back,

364
00:22:29,941 --> 00:22:33,011
every single thing you said
was right on point.

365
00:22:35,311 --> 00:22:37,681
You must have been going through
so much.

366
00:22:38,611 --> 00:22:43,151
I was worried you'd hold it in,
but I'm glad you let it out.

367
00:22:44,121 --> 00:22:45,151
But still...

368
00:22:46,051 --> 00:22:47,191
I'm sorry.

369
00:22:48,661 --> 00:22:50,761
Don't worry,
we'll sort everything out.

370
00:22:51,131 --> 00:22:52,731
Just go and apologize to your uncle.

371
00:22:53,431 --> 00:22:54,431
Okay.

372
00:22:58,301 --> 00:23:00,571
- Ju Ah.
- Yes, Grandma?

373
00:23:02,501 --> 00:23:06,011
I liked Hyun Bin too, you know.

374
00:23:08,211 --> 00:23:11,581
Please understand
that's just how things had to be.

375
00:23:13,721 --> 00:23:14,721
Okay.

376
00:23:25,191 --> 00:23:28,861
Are you sure you are done with
left Jeong Han's daughter?

377
00:23:28,861 --> 00:23:29,861
Yes.

378
00:23:30,601 --> 00:23:34,671
I'm never seeing her again.
So please, never bring her up again.

379
00:23:35,401 --> 00:23:37,671
- Is that true?
- Yes.

380
00:23:38,441 --> 00:23:41,141
Well, all right.
If you say you broke up,

381
00:23:42,581 --> 00:23:45,781
just pull yourself together
and find a good match in the future.

382
00:23:45,881 --> 00:23:47,151
I'm not getting married.

383
00:23:47,951 --> 00:23:51,621
- What?
- I don't intend to date again.

384
00:23:52,921 --> 00:23:54,121
Hyun Bin.

385
00:23:54,461 --> 00:23:56,931
When Ju Ah and I broke up,

386
00:23:56,931 --> 00:23:59,461
she asked me to protect
Fashion Division.

387
00:23:59,861 --> 00:24:02,161
My only goal will be
to keep that promise.

388
00:24:02,361 --> 00:24:05,331
If you ever bring up
women to me again,

389
00:24:05,931 --> 00:24:08,001
I will never set foot
in this house again. Understood?

390
00:24:24,091 --> 00:24:25,091
Mom.

391
00:24:28,891 --> 00:24:30,691
Why are you still up?

392
00:24:32,131 --> 00:24:33,131
You're awake?

393
00:24:33,461 --> 00:24:35,331
Can't you sleep?

394
00:24:37,001 --> 00:24:38,001
A little.

395
00:24:40,841 --> 00:24:43,871
Something happened today, didn't it?

396
00:24:44,611 --> 00:24:47,441
When you came in earlier,
it looked like you'd been crying.

397
00:24:49,341 --> 00:24:51,681
No, it's nothing. Nothing happened.

398
00:24:57,951 --> 00:24:58,951
Min Seo.

399
00:24:59,691 --> 00:25:00,691
Yes?

400
00:25:01,261 --> 00:25:04,531
What if I went to the US with you?

401
00:25:09,061 --> 00:25:11,071
Never mind.
I was just thinking out loud.

402
00:25:11,071 --> 00:25:12,101
Go back to sleep.

403
00:25:18,041 --> 00:25:22,311
Goodness, you just quit your job.
Why on earth are you up so early?

404
00:25:22,411 --> 00:25:25,811
- Can't sleep in. Got an interview.
- You do?

405
00:25:25,881 --> 00:25:26,881
Already?

406
00:25:27,351 --> 00:25:29,551
Mom, are you okay?

407
00:25:29,851 --> 00:25:31,891
Well, it took you
long enough to ask.

408
00:25:32,291 --> 00:25:33,551
So, have you learned your lesson?

409
00:25:34,461 --> 00:25:38,861
Do you think I should
apologize to his family?

410
00:25:39,261 --> 00:25:43,061
No, don't. I'll take care of it.
Just go apologize to your uncle.

411
00:25:47,041 --> 00:25:49,841
Well, well, if it isn't
Ms. Anger Management, Gong Ju Ah.

412
00:25:50,171 --> 00:25:52,911
Uncle, I'm so, so sorry. Really.

413
00:25:54,081 --> 00:25:55,611
Honestly...

414
00:25:55,711 --> 00:25:59,311
When they were going on and on about
your mom caring for a sick person,

415
00:25:59,351 --> 00:26:02,181
I almost flipped
the entire table over myself.

416
00:26:03,351 --> 00:26:04,651
You're lying.

417
00:26:05,191 --> 00:26:06,191
You got me.

418
00:26:06,851 --> 00:26:09,321
It's okay, Ju Ah.
Don't worry so much.

419
00:26:09,721 --> 00:26:11,591
I'll smooth things over
with Dong Suk's family.

420
00:26:12,561 --> 00:26:13,701
I'm sorry.

421
00:26:14,661 --> 00:26:17,671
Wait, so you and Hyun Bin broke up,

422
00:26:18,501 --> 00:26:20,001
and now you're
even switching companies?

423
00:26:20,101 --> 00:26:23,971
Yes. But it's fine.
I'll take that scouting offer.

424
00:26:26,271 --> 00:26:27,781
I really had no idea...

425
00:26:28,481 --> 00:26:29,481
that you two were dating.

426
00:26:31,181 --> 00:26:32,811
I'm sorry, I feel like
I got in the way.

427
00:26:32,981 --> 00:26:35,721
No, not at all.
We'd already broken up by then.

428
00:26:36,751 --> 00:26:39,121
Uncle. About that,

429
00:26:39,221 --> 00:26:42,421
I hope you'll understand if I skip
family events and things like that.

430
00:26:44,731 --> 00:26:45,731
Of course.

431
00:26:47,961 --> 00:26:48,961
I got your back.

432
00:26:50,331 --> 00:26:53,531
I was just on a call with Min Seo.
She said Mom cried all night.

433
00:26:53,601 --> 00:26:54,841
What does she have to cry about?

434
00:26:55,141 --> 00:26:56,141
Grandfather!

435
00:26:56,441 --> 00:26:59,311
She also said Mom wants to go
to the US with Min Seo.

436
00:26:59,511 --> 00:27:01,511
What? The US?

437
00:27:02,781 --> 00:27:06,211
Father, why did you have to yell
at Se Ri like that?

438
00:27:06,281 --> 00:27:08,281
You're the one who messed up,
so why are you blaming me?

439
00:27:10,851 --> 00:27:13,191
Neither of you
is in the right here, okay?

440
00:27:13,291 --> 00:27:16,891
Stop fighting
and just fix this mess.

441
00:27:17,891 --> 00:27:21,931
- How are we supposed to fix this?
- Father, just stay out of this.

442
00:27:23,131 --> 00:27:26,371
Grandfather, you need to tell her
to come home right now.

443
00:27:26,571 --> 00:27:29,101
Tell her if she doesn't listen,
you'll force a divorce.

444
00:27:29,371 --> 00:27:31,071
Wait, divorce?

445
00:27:38,011 --> 00:27:39,011
What is it, Mom?

446
00:27:39,411 --> 00:27:42,351
Ji Hu, I'm going to start looking
for a place for the three of us.

447
00:27:42,821 --> 00:27:45,351
- You're planning to move out?
- Yes. Why?

448
00:27:45,851 --> 00:27:48,691
Have you thought about
moving into the manager's place?

449
00:27:49,121 --> 00:27:50,191
Oh, that...

450
00:27:50,561 --> 00:27:54,701
Ms. Na felt bad for me,
growing up without a mom,

451
00:27:54,761 --> 00:27:57,801
and she offered
to take care of me if I moved in.

452
00:27:58,571 --> 00:27:59,571
And?

453
00:27:59,871 --> 00:28:04,741
But his whole family hasn't agreed,
and more importantly,

454
00:28:04,811 --> 00:28:06,441
there's no room for you there.

455
00:28:09,281 --> 00:28:11,181
Are you all ready?
Let's go get breakfast.

456
00:28:21,691 --> 00:28:23,891
So what neighborhood do you think
we should look in?

457
00:28:24,231 --> 00:28:26,231
Definitely somewhere
close to Ji Hu's school.

458
00:28:27,361 --> 00:28:30,901
So we just need two bedrooms, right?
One for us and one for Ji Hu.

459
00:28:31,171 --> 00:28:34,071
Yes. Let's look at places
this weekend.

460
00:28:35,441 --> 00:28:37,041
But, honey,

461
00:28:37,441 --> 00:28:41,981
I don't have much saved up.
We both work, so how about a loan?

462
00:28:42,281 --> 00:28:43,581
You don't have much either, do you?

463
00:28:43,851 --> 00:28:45,611
Yes, you're right. I don't.

464
00:28:46,411 --> 00:28:47,651
But so what?

465
00:28:48,051 --> 00:28:49,581
We'll figure something out
that works for us.

466
00:28:50,921 --> 00:28:54,261
Though, moving in with
your folks makes the most sense.

467
00:28:54,321 --> 00:28:56,161
No!

468
00:28:56,621 --> 00:28:59,131
Moving in is a definite no.
Do you know how crowded my house is?

469
00:28:59,191 --> 00:29:00,191
Gosh, no way!

470
00:29:00,661 --> 00:29:02,601
Right, and there's no room
for Ji Hu. Right?

471
00:29:02,701 --> 00:29:06,401
Yes. Anyway,
I'll figure that part out, so go on.

472
00:29:06,401 --> 00:29:10,071
- You need to open the shop.
- Okay. I'll talk to you later.

473
00:29:10,541 --> 00:29:11,571
Okay.

474
00:29:16,911 --> 00:29:18,251
Gosh, what was that?

475
00:29:24,521 --> 00:29:25,591
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

476
00:29:26,791 --> 00:29:27,791
Oh, my. Se Ri!

477
00:29:29,391 --> 00:29:30,691
Dong Suk.

478
00:29:35,801 --> 00:29:36,901
You're here.

479
00:29:37,731 --> 00:29:38,901
Hey, Jin Ah.

480
00:29:39,471 --> 00:29:43,911
What happened in Seongdam
with you and Officer Jeong?

481
00:29:45,341 --> 00:29:46,541
About that,

482
00:29:46,841 --> 00:29:49,341
after canvassing the shops
near the suspect tailor shop,

483
00:29:49,441 --> 00:29:51,651
we successfully pinpointed
the date they moved.

484
00:29:51,781 --> 00:29:54,321
So you're starting to
get a clearer picture?

485
00:29:54,581 --> 00:29:57,551
Yes. So we identified
nearby CCTV cameras...

486
00:29:57,621 --> 00:29:59,621
and asked the control center
to review the footage.

487
00:29:59,751 --> 00:30:04,331
- Did they find and see it?
- No.

488
00:30:04,791 --> 00:30:09,431
The retention period had expired,
so we found no significant leads.

489
00:30:11,601 --> 00:30:15,471
Anyway, we have to expand the search
to the surrounding areas,

490
00:30:15,541 --> 00:30:17,541
so it looks like the investigation
is going to drag on.

491
00:30:26,311 --> 00:30:27,551
Se Ri, are you okay?

492
00:30:29,281 --> 00:30:32,121
It looks like you've been crying.
Your eyes are all puffy.

493
00:30:33,521 --> 00:30:34,621
About yesterday,

494
00:30:35,721 --> 00:30:37,931
I'm so sorry, Dong Suk.

495
00:30:39,061 --> 00:30:41,431
It was
such an important day for you,

496
00:30:41,501 --> 00:30:44,231
but I was overwhelmed
by everything all at once.

497
00:30:45,071 --> 00:30:46,571
I wasn't thinking straight.

498
00:30:48,541 --> 00:30:49,671
I understand.

499
00:30:51,571 --> 00:30:52,811
Your father.

500
00:30:53,811 --> 00:30:55,141
He was furious, wasn't he?

501
00:30:56,181 --> 00:30:59,581
He got it all out of his system
yesterday. It's fine.

502
00:31:01,121 --> 00:31:02,421
But still, Dong Suk,

503
00:31:02,781 --> 00:31:06,021
I'm really against
you moving in with his family.

504
00:31:07,821 --> 00:31:10,261
If you live with them
from the very beginning,

505
00:31:10,391 --> 00:31:14,131
it'll be really hard to move out
on your own later.

506
00:31:14,601 --> 00:31:19,001
If you live with your in-laws,
you can't enjoy being newlyweds.

507
00:31:19,731 --> 00:31:24,511
You'll have to walk on eggshells,
and it'll be uncomfortable.

508
00:31:24,611 --> 00:31:28,041
Se Ri, were you uncomfortable
living with our family?

509
00:31:28,111 --> 00:31:30,081
No, not at all.

510
00:31:30,481 --> 00:31:34,451
For me, I was so lonely living
by myself before I got married.

511
00:31:34,581 --> 00:31:37,691
So I liked caring for a family,
but you...

512
00:31:39,421 --> 00:31:41,161
You're different.

513
00:31:41,761 --> 00:31:43,661
You did housework
for your first in-laws...

514
00:31:43,661 --> 00:31:46,231
and nursed your dying mother-in-law.

515
00:31:46,291 --> 00:31:49,831
- It was incredibly hard for you.
- My gosh.

516
00:31:50,501 --> 00:31:53,101
So that's what you meant yesterday
about caring for a sick person?

517
00:31:53,871 --> 00:31:54,871
Right.

518
00:31:55,671 --> 00:31:58,971
You're too much.
You don't really mean that.

519
00:31:59,611 --> 00:32:03,841
No, I just mean
I won't let you suffer again.

520
00:32:04,611 --> 00:32:08,621
Of course, I know
Ms. Na's family isn't like that.

521
00:32:10,351 --> 00:32:11,791
Don't worry.

522
00:32:12,121 --> 00:32:13,821
We've decided to look
for our own place.

523
00:32:15,221 --> 00:32:16,221
Really?

524
00:32:16,921 --> 00:32:19,231
Good for you.
That's a great decision.

525
00:32:20,861 --> 00:32:25,501
Min Seo is having a farewell dinner
with friends today,

526
00:32:25,571 --> 00:32:28,871
and she reserved a table with us.
She's going to the US soon, right?

527
00:32:30,171 --> 00:32:31,171
Yes.

528
00:32:32,271 --> 00:32:34,711
What'll you do when Min Seo leaves?
You'll be so lonely.

529
00:32:35,411 --> 00:32:39,451
Since everyone was so understanding,
I got to spend time with her,

530
00:32:39,681 --> 00:32:41,221
and I'm so grateful for that.

531
00:32:48,861 --> 00:32:50,291
Thank you for the drink.

532
00:32:50,891 --> 00:32:51,891
Sure.

533
00:32:53,031 --> 00:32:56,261
Are you here to give me a talking-to
for making your mom cry?

534
00:32:57,331 --> 00:32:58,671
Is it that obvious?

535
00:32:59,901 --> 00:33:01,241
I'm upset about it too.

536
00:33:01,771 --> 00:33:04,171
I'm trying my best
to smooth things over.

537
00:33:04,511 --> 00:33:08,541
Instead of trying to understand,
your mom keeps misunderstanding me.

538
00:33:08,981 --> 00:33:11,151
She knows you're sincere, Dr. Yang.

539
00:33:11,551 --> 00:33:13,611
I heard she said
she wants to go to the US.

540
00:33:13,981 --> 00:33:15,751
She must be sick of seeing me.

541
00:33:16,021 --> 00:33:17,321
She must be trying
to break up with me.

542
00:33:18,821 --> 00:33:19,951
My mom.

543
00:33:20,251 --> 00:33:22,321
She's been wanting to go home
this whole time.

544
00:33:23,621 --> 00:33:26,491
She's been worrying about
if Grandfather has been eating well,

545
00:33:26,931 --> 00:33:31,071
and if you were dressed warmly
for your last day of shooting.

546
00:33:31,131 --> 00:33:33,101
She's just been constantly worrying
about her family.

547
00:33:33,571 --> 00:33:37,511
- Really?
- Yes. And...

548
00:33:38,811 --> 00:33:41,881
when she heard the news
that grandmother passed away,

549
00:33:42,411 --> 00:33:45,511
she ran out of there
like a madwoman.

550
00:33:47,111 --> 00:33:51,691
She kept saying she had to go home,
worried your family was struggling,

551
00:33:52,321 --> 00:33:54,761
but Eun Bin and I stopped her.

552
00:33:54,961 --> 00:33:56,821
Gosh, why would you do that?

553
00:33:57,591 --> 00:34:00,031
She's extremely anxious and on edge.

554
00:34:00,761 --> 00:34:02,161
So she's somewhat...

555
00:34:02,231 --> 00:34:05,871
lashing out and expressing herself
in a negative way.

556
00:34:06,901 --> 00:34:07,971
I see.

557
00:34:08,701 --> 00:34:12,441
Couldn't you try to reach out
to her a little more?

558
00:34:13,411 --> 00:34:17,451
A woman's heart is fickle.
Who can figure it out?

559
00:34:18,751 --> 00:34:21,521
All right. I'll try harder.

560
00:34:22,481 --> 00:34:23,781
Thank you, sweetheart.

561
00:34:24,721 --> 00:34:26,921
Still, I'm glad you're here,
Min Seo.

562
00:34:27,621 --> 00:34:29,421
At least Se Ri won't be lonely.

563
00:34:32,131 --> 00:34:33,131
Hang on a second.

564
00:34:34,761 --> 00:34:35,931
Hey, Jeong Han.

565
00:34:38,071 --> 00:34:41,041
Hey, how's Seong Mi doing?

566
00:34:41,401 --> 00:34:46,241
She's okay, but her test results
weren't great, so I'm worried.

567
00:34:46,841 --> 00:34:49,241
I'm so sorry about
the family meeting yesterday.

568
00:34:49,711 --> 00:34:51,111
It was all my fault.

569
00:34:51,581 --> 00:34:53,711
You must've had
a really hard time too.

570
00:34:54,011 --> 00:34:55,781
Well, what can you do?

571
00:34:56,351 --> 00:35:00,991
Hey, you! Your son and my daughter,
Did you know they were dating?

572
00:35:01,361 --> 00:35:02,491
Of course I didn't.

573
00:35:02,961 --> 00:35:07,031
- You didn't know either?
- No. With things in my own house,

574
00:35:07,091 --> 00:35:08,701
I'm basically the last one
to find out.

575
00:35:09,461 --> 00:35:11,001
I figured as much.

576
00:35:11,831 --> 00:35:14,641
Hyun Bin gets that from me.
He's hopelessly devoted.

577
00:35:15,841 --> 00:35:18,641
Looks like he couldn't get over
his first love, just like me.

578
00:35:18,771 --> 00:35:20,571
Oh, for crying out loud!
That right there!

579
00:35:21,011 --> 00:35:24,611
That's exactly the talk
that makes your wife so upset!

580
00:35:24,751 --> 00:35:27,481
And that's why she can't stand
my Seong Mi!

581
00:35:28,581 --> 00:35:29,581
I'm sorry.

582
00:35:29,851 --> 00:35:32,191
You, when you're about
to say what's on your mind,

583
00:35:32,251 --> 00:35:35,291
you need to run it through a filter
up here before you speak!

584
00:35:37,761 --> 00:35:40,391
What am I going to do with Se Ri?

585
00:35:40,531 --> 00:35:43,031
I honestly have no idea what to do.

586
00:35:43,361 --> 00:35:46,571
Don't worry about it.
Seong Mi will handle it.

587
00:35:46,771 --> 00:35:47,771
How?

588
00:35:48,441 --> 00:35:49,571
How would I know?

589
00:35:50,171 --> 00:35:53,811
But she did say something about
getting to the root of the problem.

590
00:35:54,811 --> 00:35:55,811
The root of the problem?

591
00:35:57,951 --> 00:35:59,611
(3H Acupressure Bed)

592
00:36:03,621 --> 00:36:04,621
Welcome...

593
00:36:08,061 --> 00:36:09,061
Oh my!

594
00:36:10,721 --> 00:36:13,661
What? Surprised to see a patient?

595
00:36:16,101 --> 00:36:20,431
Stress from you made my pain worse,
so I just came from the doctor's.

596
00:36:23,171 --> 00:36:24,171
My gosh...

597
00:36:25,141 --> 00:36:26,441
So why are you here?

598
00:36:27,341 --> 00:36:31,051
You certainly don't look like
you're here to apologize for her.

599
00:36:31,681 --> 00:36:34,081
Apologize? Why would I?

600
00:36:34,481 --> 00:36:36,621
And for the record,
Ju Ah won't be apologizing either.

601
00:36:37,281 --> 00:36:41,521
After all, she's a mannerless brat
who wasn't raised right.

602
00:36:42,491 --> 00:36:47,431
- You really hold a grudge.
- You've made mistakes too.

603
00:36:47,931 --> 00:36:49,231
So let's just call it even.

604
00:36:51,031 --> 00:36:52,631
I can't believe this.

605
00:36:53,001 --> 00:36:54,201
Let me give you a warning.

606
00:36:55,301 --> 00:36:57,101
Don't you dare
mess with my daughter.

607
00:36:57,771 --> 00:37:00,141
I never disrespected
Director Yang either.

608
00:37:01,041 --> 00:37:03,781
And I didn't enjoy opposing them.

609
00:37:06,081 --> 00:37:09,781
Since they've decided to separate,
let's just support their decision.

610
00:37:10,351 --> 00:37:13,051
So, is that
what you came here to say?

611
00:37:13,751 --> 00:37:14,761
No.

612
00:37:15,221 --> 00:37:17,731
To give my husband
some peace of mind,

613
00:37:17,791 --> 00:37:20,861
I think we need to resolve
the fundamental issue between us.

614
00:37:21,401 --> 00:37:24,401
Our kids' breakup is enough,
isn't it?

615
00:37:25,671 --> 00:37:26,701
And so?

616
00:37:28,771 --> 00:37:30,171
Let's have a sit-down.
The four of us.

617
00:37:30,941 --> 00:37:32,541
A sit-down? The four of us?

618
00:37:32,941 --> 00:37:35,441
Yes. You two, and us two.

619
00:37:35,581 --> 00:37:38,051
Let's get together as couples
and hash this all out.

620
00:37:38,711 --> 00:37:39,711
Well...

621
00:37:40,711 --> 00:37:42,151
Be my guest.

622
00:37:43,281 --> 00:37:44,891
And just so we're clear,

623
00:37:45,721 --> 00:37:50,461
ever since college, I've never had
any interest in Dr. Yang.

624
00:37:51,591 --> 00:37:53,361
I was the campus queen,

625
00:37:53,431 --> 00:37:56,261
and honestly,
Dr. Yang was a total nobody.

626
00:37:59,801 --> 00:38:00,801
That's rich.

627
00:38:02,471 --> 00:38:05,611
You know what they call people
like you these days?

628
00:38:06,241 --> 00:38:09,141
A "squid keeper."

629
00:38:14,351 --> 00:38:15,681
Squid...

630
00:38:16,251 --> 00:38:17,251
keeper?

631
00:38:18,191 --> 00:38:19,291
Squid?

632
00:38:19,921 --> 00:38:22,721
What? My husband is a squid?
What is she talking about?

633
00:38:23,021 --> 00:38:25,631
Keeping a squid?
I can't believe her.

634
00:38:30,631 --> 00:38:31,631
I heard your mom...

635
00:38:32,001 --> 00:38:34,331
had it out with Ms. Gong, then you,
one after the other.

636
00:38:35,471 --> 00:38:36,471
No thanks.

637
00:38:36,541 --> 00:38:37,701
(Taehan Group)

638
00:38:38,211 --> 00:38:40,871
Seriously,
does everyone in the company know?

639
00:38:41,781 --> 00:38:43,111
What do you expect
when you fight at the office?

640
00:38:43,641 --> 00:38:46,251
I'll make sure
it won't happen again.

641
00:38:48,051 --> 00:38:49,621
So what was that all about?

642
00:38:50,221 --> 00:38:51,221
Was it because of Ms. Gong?

643
00:38:53,451 --> 00:38:56,421
What? Why the death stare?

644
00:38:56,791 --> 00:38:59,131
From now on,
we don't talk about Ms. Gong.

645
00:39:00,691 --> 00:39:02,631
Gosh, there goes
my only fun at work.

646
00:39:02,801 --> 00:39:04,771
Is this really the time for jokes?

647
00:39:05,071 --> 00:39:08,471
- Do you think this is a joke?
- Okay, I get it.

648
00:39:09,171 --> 00:39:11,441
Any movement from Director Baek?
Are you looking into it?

649
00:39:11,441 --> 00:39:14,711
Yes. I'm trying to figure out
his motive first.

650
00:39:15,281 --> 00:39:16,281
Be careful.

651
00:39:17,541 --> 00:39:19,711
That guy has eyes
in the back of his head.

652
00:39:20,581 --> 00:39:21,581
I know.

653
00:39:22,481 --> 00:39:23,751
By the way, where'd Mr. Park go?

654
00:39:24,591 --> 00:39:25,591
Golfing.

655
00:39:26,091 --> 00:39:27,751
- Who with?
- Director Baek.

656
00:39:28,321 --> 00:39:29,321
What?

657
00:39:29,421 --> 00:39:31,731
Why were you out golfing
in the middle of a workday?

658
00:39:33,631 --> 00:39:36,501
I was chosen to be
an undercover agent...

659
00:39:36,901 --> 00:39:38,801
to keep an eye on Director Baek.

660
00:39:40,971 --> 00:39:42,001
What are you talking about?

661
00:39:42,871 --> 00:39:45,271
I'm telling you, Director Yang.

662
00:39:45,571 --> 00:39:49,381
He's going to do whatever it takes
to protect our Fashion Division,

663
00:39:49,441 --> 00:39:51,011
and he's risking everything,
so don't worry.

664
00:39:51,881 --> 00:39:52,881
I'm not worried.

665
00:39:54,651 --> 00:39:56,381
So, how did
your Ceviel interview go?

666
00:39:56,981 --> 00:39:59,251
Of course.
They seemed to really like me.

667
00:40:00,691 --> 00:40:02,191
If they make you an offer,

668
00:40:02,891 --> 00:40:04,261
are you really going to take it
and work there?

669
00:40:04,861 --> 00:40:08,461
They're strongly considering it,
so I probably will.

670
00:40:09,101 --> 00:40:12,301
Darn it. Deep down,
our team was hoping...

671
00:40:12,371 --> 00:40:14,641
you wouldn't get the job.

672
00:40:15,341 --> 00:40:16,341
Why?

673
00:40:16,841 --> 00:40:19,811
Everyone knows what a shark you are.
Isn't it obvious?

674
00:40:20,111 --> 00:40:23,211
You're a great ally,
but a terrifying enemy.

675
00:40:24,011 --> 00:40:28,221
Come on, a little competition
helps us grow. It's a good thing.

676
00:40:29,181 --> 00:40:30,681
Give me a break.

677
00:40:33,551 --> 00:40:35,991
So what am I supposed to do?

678
00:40:36,391 --> 00:40:40,661
Hey, did I ask you?
Why are you telling me that?

679
00:40:41,331 --> 00:40:42,331
Just hang up!

680
00:40:43,701 --> 00:40:44,701
Darn it.

681
00:40:45,031 --> 00:40:47,171
Gosh, who was on the phone?

682
00:40:47,701 --> 00:40:49,371
The Vice President.

683
00:40:50,201 --> 00:40:55,111
But still, how could you get so mad
at the Vice President?

684
00:40:55,241 --> 00:40:59,681
She found out her interview results
through Ms. Kim.

685
00:40:59,911 --> 00:41:01,781
What happened?

686
00:41:02,081 --> 00:41:07,021
- She was rejected.
- And Gong Ju Ah thought she had it.

687
00:41:07,991 --> 00:41:09,221
What are we going to do,
Director Yang?

688
00:41:09,721 --> 00:41:12,331
What do you mean? Why should I care?

689
00:41:12,661 --> 00:41:13,831
Gosh, what's with him?

690
00:41:14,231 --> 00:41:17,131
Don't mention her name again.
Got it?

691
00:41:17,901 --> 00:41:20,731
Director Yang,
I think you might have developed...

692
00:41:20,931 --> 00:41:23,601
some anger management issues.

693
00:41:27,811 --> 00:41:30,781
How did the round of golf go?
Report.

694
00:41:33,381 --> 00:41:34,621
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

695
00:41:34,681 --> 00:41:38,791
- What a beautiful day!
- Wow, it's so nice out.

696
00:41:40,021 --> 00:41:41,051
Thank you, friends,

697
00:41:41,121 --> 00:41:43,191
for coming to my farewell party
today.

698
00:41:43,721 --> 00:41:45,491
And this is...

699
00:41:45,731 --> 00:41:48,731
Eun Bin, my birth mom's daughter
I met in Korea.

700
00:41:49,761 --> 00:41:54,471
Hi, friends.
For being friends with our Min Seo,

701
00:41:54,531 --> 00:41:58,111
thank you all so much.
Thank you so much, everyone.

702
00:41:59,271 --> 00:42:00,971
She's really cute, right?

703
00:42:02,611 --> 00:42:04,751
- Am I cute?
- Yes.

704
00:42:05,081 --> 00:42:06,081
Thank you.

705
00:42:06,611 --> 00:42:10,321
Okay, everyone,
I'll grill the meat for you, okay?

706
00:42:10,381 --> 00:42:11,491
Wow!

707
00:42:12,021 --> 00:42:13,021
I'll do the grilling.

708
00:42:13,321 --> 00:42:15,521
- I'm good at it.
- Eun Bin,

709
00:42:15,791 --> 00:42:19,631
this is Jason,
the creative director I mentioned.

710
00:42:25,101 --> 00:42:26,831
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

711
00:42:41,821 --> 00:42:44,181
Wow. Very, very delicious.

712
00:42:46,191 --> 00:42:49,261
Korean barbecue is really
something special.

713
00:42:49,921 --> 00:42:52,561
It's delicious, right?
This meat is aged.

714
00:42:53,491 --> 00:42:55,431
How long have you been on YouTube?

715
00:42:56,001 --> 00:42:57,001
How many subscribers?

716
00:42:57,061 --> 00:43:01,341
I started about three years ago,

717
00:43:01,741 --> 00:43:04,841
and my subscribers, if I round up,

718
00:43:05,271 --> 00:43:07,011
is around 300.

719
00:43:08,681 --> 00:43:09,681
I see.

720
00:43:10,211 --> 00:43:11,981
What's your main content?

721
00:43:12,411 --> 00:43:16,821
I mainly review clothing brands...

722
00:43:16,921 --> 00:43:19,721
and daily vlogs.
A little bit of everything.

723
00:43:19,821 --> 00:43:23,691
That's too scattered.
I can give you some real help.

724
00:43:24,461 --> 00:43:26,091
Really? You'd do that for me?

725
00:43:26,431 --> 00:43:28,461
Then I should definitely treat you
to something nice today.

726
00:43:29,161 --> 00:43:33,771
Anything else you guys want to eat?
It's a better deal the more we get.

727
00:43:37,741 --> 00:43:40,471
Let's get this and what else?

728
00:43:48,281 --> 00:43:50,451
- Min Seo? What do you need?
- I just need some water.

729
00:43:52,551 --> 00:43:55,091
Thanks for drumming up business,
sweetie.

730
00:43:55,821 --> 00:43:56,821
Not at all.

731
00:43:57,421 --> 00:44:00,731
Can't believe it's my goodbye party.
Once I go back to the US,

732
00:44:00,791 --> 00:44:03,661
- I'll worry about Ji Hu's tutoring.
- I know, right?

733
00:44:06,071 --> 00:44:07,071
Woo Jae,

734
00:44:07,631 --> 00:44:11,441
after I leave, would you perhaps
be interested in tutoring Ji Hu?

735
00:44:13,071 --> 00:44:14,071
Well...

736
00:44:18,611 --> 00:44:21,921
Ma'am, so you saw the show.
Thank you.

737
00:44:22,421 --> 00:44:24,351
Is that how it came across?

738
00:44:26,551 --> 00:44:30,891
Ma'am, my husband isn't
unlikable at all, I promise.

739
00:44:31,221 --> 00:44:33,661
It was an act to make...

740
00:44:33,661 --> 00:44:35,631
Councilor Hwang stand out
on the show.

741
00:44:35,861 --> 00:44:40,031
You know how someone looks
better next to someone unlikable.

742
00:44:41,601 --> 00:44:44,101
Of course, Ma'am. Yes.

743
00:44:44,171 --> 00:44:46,641
We should play a round of golf
before it gets too hot.

744
00:44:47,141 --> 00:44:48,141
Yes, okay.

745
00:44:49,741 --> 00:44:50,741
You startled me.

746
00:44:51,451 --> 00:44:52,781
When did you get here?

747
00:44:54,551 --> 00:44:55,581
Just now.

748
00:44:56,321 --> 00:44:58,791
Were you on the phone with
Councilor Hwang's wife?

749
00:44:59,451 --> 00:45:02,391
Just because we're separated...

750
00:45:03,421 --> 00:45:06,191
doesn't mean I'll choose a stranger
over you. Whatever.

751
00:45:06,831 --> 00:45:08,431
- Thank you...
- What?

752
00:45:09,961 --> 00:45:11,001
Why are you here?

753
00:45:13,401 --> 00:45:15,571
Father told me to bring you home.

754
00:45:23,941 --> 00:45:24,951
Father,

755
00:45:25,651 --> 00:45:27,411
I was terribly wrong yesterday.

756
00:45:28,451 --> 00:45:30,981
I told Min Seo to pack her things
and come here.

757
00:45:32,291 --> 00:45:34,321
- What?
- What do you mean, "What?"

758
00:45:35,821 --> 00:45:37,191
Do you never want to see me again?

759
00:45:38,191 --> 00:45:39,361
Are you two going to split up?

760
00:45:39,931 --> 00:45:42,561
No, that's not it.

761
00:45:42,831 --> 00:45:45,031
If you're not getting a divorce,
then you share a bed.

762
00:45:45,401 --> 00:45:46,401
Bicker and fight all you want,

763
00:45:47,201 --> 00:45:48,371
but if you're not getting a divorce,

764
00:45:50,701 --> 00:45:51,911
you're not leaving this house again.

765
00:46:00,281 --> 00:46:01,281
Honey.

766
00:46:02,721 --> 00:46:05,991
I was wrong to get
Seong Mi's counseling. I'm sorry.

767
00:46:06,221 --> 00:46:08,761
I honestly had no idea
you'd take it that way, okay?

768
00:46:10,561 --> 00:46:12,491
Dr. Han suggested
a four-way meeting.

769
00:46:13,131 --> 00:46:14,361
Yes, I heard that.

770
00:46:15,101 --> 00:46:17,661
She said we should resolve
the root of the problem.

771
00:46:18,131 --> 00:46:19,331
I have no idea
what that's supposed to mean.

772
00:46:19,831 --> 00:46:21,941
But anyway, from now on,

773
00:46:22,641 --> 00:46:24,541
I'll never do anything you dislike.

774
00:46:24,541 --> 00:46:26,171
And before I act,

775
00:46:26,171 --> 00:46:27,611
I promise I'll always talk
to you first.

776
00:46:30,711 --> 00:46:31,751
I mean...

777
00:46:32,011 --> 00:46:34,611
Honey, please forgive me.

778
00:46:35,681 --> 00:46:38,451
Let's end this separation now...

779
00:46:39,091 --> 00:46:41,761
and work this out together
happily, okay?

780
00:46:43,321 --> 00:46:45,461
How about some
under-the-covers cuddles?

781
00:46:46,061 --> 00:46:47,861
Want to cuddle?

782
00:46:50,861 --> 00:46:52,971
Who said our separation is ending?
Says who?

783
00:46:53,301 --> 00:46:57,171
Sorry. You can have the bed.
I'll sleep on the floor.

784
00:47:14,451 --> 00:47:16,291
I'm packing my things
and moving into my studio.

785
00:47:17,091 --> 00:47:18,291
Yang Hyun Bin! Son!

786
00:47:19,931 --> 00:47:20,931
What?

787
00:47:21,761 --> 00:47:23,861
Aren't you going to apologize to me?

788
00:47:24,361 --> 00:47:25,671
You should apologize to me, Mother.

789
00:47:26,371 --> 00:47:28,941
- What?
- What did I do wrong?

790
00:47:29,271 --> 00:47:31,201
You're the one who came to my office
and caused a scene.

791
00:47:31,611 --> 00:47:33,541
Me? A scene?

792
00:47:33,941 --> 00:47:35,641
Yes, a scene.

793
00:47:36,141 --> 00:47:39,381
The rumors are all over the office.
Thanks to you, I can't show my face.

794
00:47:39,651 --> 00:47:41,211
So you're the one
who needs to apologize.

795
00:47:42,151 --> 00:47:43,151
Hyun Bin.

796
00:47:43,651 --> 00:47:45,151
What? Are your feelings hurt?

797
00:47:45,751 --> 00:47:48,151
I'm the one who's upset. Me.

798
00:47:48,221 --> 00:47:52,791
Because of you, I left Ms. Gong.
She was the only love of my life.

799
00:47:52,931 --> 00:47:54,791
And I had to give her up
because of you!

800
00:47:55,361 --> 00:47:56,361
You.

801
00:47:56,801 --> 00:47:59,071
How could you
possibly say that to me?

802
00:47:59,771 --> 00:48:01,571
You don't see me
as your mother, do you?

803
00:48:01,771 --> 00:48:04,241
No. To be honest, until now,
I never saw you as my mother.

804
00:48:04,241 --> 00:48:09,281
You're not my birth mother,
just my young stepmother.

805
00:48:09,281 --> 00:48:11,481
But now
the adoption is official, right?

806
00:48:11,611 --> 00:48:14,281
I'll treat you like my real mother
and act like a real son.

807
00:48:15,921 --> 00:48:17,721
- What?
- From now on,

808
00:48:18,221 --> 00:48:20,291
if you try to interfere
or meddle in my life,

809
00:48:20,651 --> 00:48:24,021
I'll throw a tantrum like Eun Bin.
Got it?

810
00:48:24,991 --> 00:48:27,291
You. I can't believe you.

811
00:48:28,401 --> 00:48:29,401
One more thing!

812
00:48:30,361 --> 00:48:34,531
I'm changing my apartment code.
Don't just show up unannounced.

813
00:48:34,731 --> 00:48:35,741
Got it?

814
00:48:40,811 --> 00:48:42,381
Unbelievable.

815
00:48:45,381 --> 00:48:46,911
No way, was I really like that?

816
00:48:47,481 --> 00:48:49,521
But is that really
the Hyun Bin I know?

817
00:48:53,951 --> 00:48:54,951
Dong Suk, what are we going to do?

818
00:48:56,291 --> 00:48:58,931
The loan we qualify for
isn't as much as I'd hoped.

819
00:49:00,131 --> 00:49:01,131
In that case,

820
00:49:02,361 --> 00:49:03,361
what about my family's house?

821
00:49:03,661 --> 00:49:05,431
Once Min Seo leaves for the US,
there will be an empty room.

822
00:49:05,501 --> 00:49:06,531
No, we can't do that.

823
00:49:06,971 --> 00:49:10,301
Moving out is
on your bucket list. So no.

824
00:49:11,541 --> 00:49:14,341
You two should just move in
with Ms. Na.

825
00:49:15,041 --> 00:49:16,041
Son.

826
00:49:17,741 --> 00:49:18,751
Are you done with cram school today?

827
00:49:21,011 --> 00:49:23,381
We can't move in together.
There's no room at our place.

828
00:49:23,821 --> 00:49:26,591
You don't need a room for me.
Because I'm not going to live there.

829
00:49:27,021 --> 00:49:29,161
- Ji Hu.
- What are you talking about?

830
00:49:29,721 --> 00:49:31,461
Don't you know we're only a family
when it's the three of us?

831
00:49:31,761 --> 00:49:33,261
I have a mom,

832
00:49:33,691 --> 00:49:37,101
but I always felt bad that Mom
doesn't have a mother of her own.

833
00:49:38,261 --> 00:49:41,671
And Ms. Na said she'd be
like a grandma and care for her,

834
00:49:42,171 --> 00:49:44,841
so I want Mom to go
live in that house.

835
00:49:45,811 --> 00:49:46,811
Ji Hu.

836
00:49:47,271 --> 00:49:48,271
Good grief.

837
00:49:48,641 --> 00:49:51,811
And I know you want to take
good care of your wife.

838
00:49:53,581 --> 00:49:54,581
That's still a no.

839
00:49:55,051 --> 00:49:57,551
I don't want my study
environment to change.

840
00:49:58,321 --> 00:50:02,921
Besides, if Mom and I both move out,
Grandpa will be too lonely.

841
00:50:04,191 --> 00:50:07,391
- I know you love Grandpa, but...
- No, Mom.

842
00:50:08,091 --> 00:50:11,031
I'm going to stay by Grandpa's side
and inherit the family clinic.

843
00:50:12,631 --> 00:50:13,831
I'm being serious right now.

844
00:50:22,511 --> 00:50:24,681
Is Mom asleep?

845
00:50:24,811 --> 00:50:28,051
Yes. She definitely sleeps
better in this house.

846
00:50:28,951 --> 00:50:33,191
All this talk about separate rooms,
when it's the last thing they want.

847
00:50:34,421 --> 00:50:36,061
So why are you up?

848
00:50:36,621 --> 00:50:39,331
Eun Bin, when I go back to the US,

849
00:50:39,431 --> 00:50:41,861
Woo Jae will take over
tutoring Ji Hu for me.

850
00:50:42,461 --> 00:50:43,461
What?

851
00:50:44,101 --> 00:50:46,871
So he'll be coming over here, then?

852
00:50:47,431 --> 00:50:48,431
Yes.

853
00:50:52,641 --> 00:50:56,241
Looks like I'm finishing
my second "assignment" before I go.

854
00:50:56,941 --> 00:51:00,811
Don't tell me your next job
is me and Woo Jae.

855
00:51:08,021 --> 00:51:09,391
So...

856
00:51:10,021 --> 00:51:11,861
So if you all move in together,

857
00:51:12,691 --> 00:51:14,761
does that mean I have
to live with the boss?

858
00:51:15,801 --> 00:51:18,361
Why? What's wrong?
Would that make you uncomfortable?

859
00:51:20,131 --> 00:51:21,631
No, not at all. I'd love that.

860
00:51:23,101 --> 00:51:26,211
Hey, with my boss as my aunt,
I'll have some solid backup.

861
00:51:26,811 --> 00:51:27,811
What about you, Ju Ah?

862
00:51:28,011 --> 00:51:31,141
It's fine. They likely won't come up
to the second floor much anyway.

863
00:51:32,351 --> 00:51:34,381
But are you really okay
with it, Mom?

864
00:51:35,481 --> 00:51:36,981
I'm fine, but...

865
00:51:37,521 --> 00:51:40,351
This talk about taking care of me
if I get sick is bothering me.

866
00:51:41,351 --> 00:51:45,191
Dae Han, if we live together,
please don't worry about me.

867
00:51:45,261 --> 00:51:47,891
- Okay?
- But how could I not?

868
00:51:48,331 --> 00:51:50,361
Should I say I'm against
this move, then?

869
00:51:50,831 --> 00:51:51,831
No.

870
00:51:54,171 --> 00:51:57,871
Even if we're careful, our families
are bound to clash over things.

871
00:51:58,171 --> 00:51:59,811
Are you all really sure
you'll be okay?

872
00:52:01,241 --> 00:52:04,741
We'll have to watch what we say,
living together.

873
00:52:05,281 --> 00:52:09,221
We'll meet Dong Ik and his wife
to work things out.

874
00:52:09,751 --> 00:52:10,751
Good.

875
00:52:11,221 --> 00:52:14,451
Thank you all for being
so understanding.

876
00:52:15,291 --> 00:52:19,491
So, when is she moving in?
Are you registering right away?

877
00:52:19,991 --> 00:52:22,161
Yes, that seems to be the plan.

878
00:52:22,361 --> 00:52:24,801
Mom, they say
the search for Father...

879
00:52:25,001 --> 00:52:27,531
is highly likely
to take a long time.

880
00:52:28,071 --> 00:52:31,771
- Really?
- Yes, Officer Jeong said so.

881
00:52:41,111 --> 00:52:43,951
Honey. This zipper here is...

882
00:52:50,161 --> 00:52:52,461
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic,
Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

883
00:53:09,681 --> 00:53:12,881
- Why would you do that?
- You're slacking off, aren't you?

884
00:53:13,951 --> 00:53:15,111
You're just sitting here
watching TV!

885
00:53:16,581 --> 00:53:17,581
How can you do this to me?

886
00:53:18,621 --> 00:53:20,821
Can't you see
how much I'm struggling?

887
00:53:21,321 --> 00:53:22,761
I was so worried
you would get caught...

888
00:53:23,061 --> 00:53:25,461
by the police and go to jail,

889
00:53:25,731 --> 00:53:27,561
so we've been on the run
for 30 years,

890
00:53:28,231 --> 00:53:30,931
and we live like beggars
without a penny to our name!

891
00:53:31,531 --> 00:53:32,831
I'm sorry.

892
00:53:35,471 --> 00:53:37,471
Just hurry up and finish.
They're waiting.

893
00:53:40,741 --> 00:53:43,411
How can you be so ungrateful?

894
00:53:44,641 --> 00:53:46,281
Gosh, seriously!

895
00:53:47,051 --> 00:53:48,251
Get back to work. Now!

896
00:54:10,341 --> 00:54:12,711
- Hello there.
- Yes, hello.

897
00:54:13,171 --> 00:54:14,241
- Hello! It's been a while.
- Good to see you.

898
00:54:14,311 --> 00:54:15,611
- Hello.
- Yes. Hello.

899
00:54:17,011 --> 00:54:20,711
I'm worried Dr. Gong's search
isn't progressing as I'd hoped.

900
00:54:20,951 --> 00:54:22,421
I know. It's frustrating.

901
00:54:24,081 --> 00:54:25,181
A call.

902
00:54:26,721 --> 00:54:27,721
There.

903
00:54:28,291 --> 00:54:29,491
Yes, Detective Jang.

904
00:54:30,461 --> 00:54:32,761
Yes. Did you find anything?

905
00:54:33,961 --> 00:54:34,961
Is that right?

906
00:54:36,931 --> 00:54:40,371
Wait. He was living with a woman?

907
00:54:40,501 --> 00:54:43,771
Yes. All the local merchants
are saying the same thing.

908
00:54:44,141 --> 00:54:46,071
Apparently, he told people
she was his younger sister.

909
00:54:46,771 --> 00:54:50,481
That's impossible.
He doesn't have a younger sister.

910
00:54:51,311 --> 00:54:54,211
Then are you saying
that man wasn't my husband?

911
00:54:54,711 --> 00:54:57,981
It's too early to say for sure.

912
00:54:59,921 --> 00:55:01,021
Still...

913
00:55:01,951 --> 00:55:04,291
It's a strange coincidence.

914
00:55:04,791 --> 00:55:06,061
What is?

915
00:55:06,461 --> 00:55:07,461
It's just that...

916
00:55:08,031 --> 00:55:11,231
I know someone
who lives in Seongdam,

917
00:55:11,601 --> 00:55:13,831
and she runs a tailor shop, too.

918
00:55:13,931 --> 00:55:17,101
I heard she lives
with her brother there.

919
00:55:17,101 --> 00:55:18,271
Really?

920
00:55:19,141 --> 00:55:22,281
But no, it couldn't be them.

921
00:55:22,941 --> 00:55:25,881
I've known her for a very long time.

922
00:55:26,651 --> 00:55:31,221
Police are trying to ID the woman
and see if she's really his sister,

923
00:55:31,551 --> 00:55:32,821
so we'll let you know
once it's confirmed.

924
00:55:33,591 --> 00:55:37,261
But just in case, what's her name?

925
00:55:38,021 --> 00:55:40,231
It's Mi Hyang. Jo Mi Hyang.

926
00:55:40,761 --> 00:55:42,861
I don't know her brother's name.

927
00:55:51,871 --> 00:55:53,141
Oh, wait. It's from Ceviel.

928
00:55:54,571 --> 00:55:55,911
Team Lead Gong Ju Ah.

929
00:55:56,211 --> 00:55:59,451
I wonder when I'll start.
All right, let's see.

930
00:56:00,251 --> 00:56:02,351
"After careful consideration,"

931
00:56:02,351 --> 00:56:04,951
"we'll reach out
for another chance..."

932
00:56:06,391 --> 00:56:09,461
What? Did I just get rejected?

933
00:56:11,591 --> 00:56:12,591
Gosh.

934
00:56:14,931 --> 00:56:16,831
- Thank you.
- Take care.

935
00:56:17,501 --> 00:56:18,501
Gosh.

936
00:56:21,831 --> 00:56:23,841
Undercover Mr. Park Jun Hyeok.

937
00:56:25,471 --> 00:56:26,471
Where are you?

938
00:56:26,871 --> 00:56:29,981
What do you think?
I'm getting popcorn, I'm starving.

939
00:56:30,341 --> 00:56:34,481
Eat up. You'll need your strength
for the job hunt.

940
00:56:35,081 --> 00:56:37,981
What? How did you know
I didn't get the job at Ceviel?

941
00:56:38,991 --> 00:56:43,121
- The Vice President called Ceviel.
- Gosh, why?

942
00:56:43,521 --> 00:56:46,491
Why would she do that? Seriously.

943
00:56:47,291 --> 00:56:48,461
Director Yang knows too.

944
00:56:49,561 --> 00:56:53,131
What if he knows?
What's that got to do with me?

945
00:56:53,401 --> 00:56:54,801
What you made is so good, Mom.

946
00:56:55,401 --> 00:56:57,341
- Why?
- It's Director Yang's mother.

947
00:57:01,271 --> 00:57:03,381
Mom, how does it feel
to be done with the separation?

948
00:57:03,741 --> 00:57:07,481
We're not done with the separation.
I'm just pretending for Grandfather.

949
00:57:08,081 --> 00:57:09,881
Mom, please.

950
00:57:10,221 --> 00:57:14,391
It's about your father. I'm furious.
I was being so humiliated,

951
00:57:14,451 --> 00:57:16,291
and he didn't take
my side even once.

952
00:57:16,291 --> 00:57:19,331
What was Gong Ju Ah thinking?

953
00:57:19,961 --> 00:57:23,001
If I ever see her around here,
she's going to get it.

954
00:57:23,231 --> 00:57:25,461
- Mom, please.
- Seriously.

955
00:57:29,941 --> 00:57:31,171
Oh my, that scared me.

956
00:57:33,341 --> 00:57:34,671
(Secret Biogen)

957
00:57:34,741 --> 00:57:36,111
(Taehan Group)

958
00:57:36,181 --> 00:57:37,341
Mr. Park Jun Hyeok.

959
00:57:37,641 --> 00:57:39,251
These are his paternity
test results.

960
00:57:47,751 --> 00:57:50,061
(DNA Parentage Test Report)

961
00:57:50,891 --> 00:57:51,891
(DNA Parentage Test Report)

962
00:57:53,291 --> 00:57:55,561
(Subject one, Hwangbo Jae Hoon)

963
00:57:55,631 --> 00:57:57,161
(Subject two, Park Jun Hyeok)

964
00:58:04,441 --> 00:58:06,571
(DNA Parentage Test Report)

965
00:58:08,341 --> 00:58:10,581
(Shared Alleles)

966
00:58:17,381 --> 00:58:20,021
Director Baek is trying to sell off
the Fashion Division?

967
00:58:22,291 --> 00:58:24,121
The nerve of him,
trying to sell off the division.

968
00:58:24,821 --> 00:58:25,861
I'm in total shock.

969
00:58:26,791 --> 00:58:28,031
It's just absurd.

970
00:58:30,031 --> 00:58:31,261
How did you find out?

971
00:58:31,931 --> 00:58:33,531
Did our undercover man,
Mr. Park, tell you?

972
00:58:33,871 --> 00:58:37,241
No, Claramont in Paris
asked me about it.

973
00:58:37,441 --> 00:58:41,371
They heard their rival, Nouvel Vian,
is trying to acquire our group,

974
00:58:41,441 --> 00:58:42,611
and asked me if it was true.

975
00:58:43,211 --> 00:58:44,341
He's completely lost it.

976
00:58:45,881 --> 00:58:47,581
He planned to sell it on the sly...

977
00:58:47,581 --> 00:58:49,321
while feeding fake information
to Mr. Park?

978
00:58:51,381 --> 00:58:53,221
I guess he wanted to
make us lower our guard.

979
00:58:59,891 --> 00:59:01,191
You wanted to see me, Director Baek?

980
00:59:02,031 --> 00:59:03,061
Well, well.

981
00:59:03,701 --> 00:59:04,801
Mr. Park.

982
00:59:05,061 --> 00:59:06,731
Director Baek,
why are you standing up?

983
00:59:12,101 --> 00:59:13,571
I had a hunch,

984
00:59:14,341 --> 00:59:15,611
but I can't believe
this is happening.

985
00:59:21,351 --> 00:59:22,981
No wonder I took a liking to you.

986
00:59:23,821 --> 00:59:25,481
Hwangbo Jun Hyeok.

987
00:59:30,191 --> 00:59:31,191
Excuse me?

988
00:59:40,131 --> 00:59:41,231
There he is.

989
00:59:50,011 --> 00:59:51,111
Quick, over here.

990
00:59:53,151 --> 00:59:55,111
The Chairman can be so cold.

991
00:59:57,821 --> 01:00:00,821
Not even looking for his own son
until he's a grown man.

992
01:00:03,061 --> 01:00:05,061
So...

993
01:00:06,091 --> 01:00:08,591
are you telling me my father,
the one you said was a tailor,

994
01:00:09,201 --> 01:00:13,101
is Chairman Hwangbo Jae Hoon
of Taehan Group?

995
01:00:15,331 --> 01:00:16,341
I...

996
01:00:17,371 --> 01:00:18,501
on a hunch...

997
01:00:19,341 --> 01:00:20,341
looked into it.

998
01:00:27,181 --> 01:00:29,951
(DNA Parentage Test Report)

999
01:00:33,021 --> 01:00:34,121
(Test Results)

1000
01:00:34,191 --> 01:00:35,291
(Hwangbo Jae Hoon
and Park Jun Hyeok...)

1001
01:00:35,351 --> 01:00:36,621
(are consistent with
a parent-child relationship.)

1002
01:00:38,991 --> 01:00:40,531
(The results show a biological
parent-child relationship.)

1003
01:00:40,891 --> 01:00:45,401
The Chairman is on his deathbed.
You wouldn't have known without me.

1004
01:00:49,101 --> 01:00:51,801
It just doesn't feel real to me,

1005
01:00:52,871 --> 01:00:55,371
I'm not sure how to react.

1006
01:00:56,311 --> 01:00:59,181
Raised by a single mother
without a father,

1007
01:00:59,811 --> 01:01:01,611
you must have had it so rough.

1008
01:01:03,321 --> 01:01:05,791
If I were you,
I'd feel so resentful and furious.

1009
01:01:06,491 --> 01:01:08,651
I bet you didn't get a single cent
of support,

1010
01:01:09,291 --> 01:01:12,691
while Hye Su lived it up
as the sole heiress.

1011
01:01:13,991 --> 01:01:17,661
You were close, yet you didn't know
she took what should've been yours.

1012
01:01:18,261 --> 01:01:20,371
It's such a cruel twist of fate.

1013
01:01:21,671 --> 01:01:22,701
Don't you think?

1014
01:01:27,241 --> 01:01:29,341
(The results show a biological
parent-child relationship.)

1015
01:01:34,351 --> 01:01:35,411
Undercover.

1016
01:01:36,251 --> 01:01:38,351
So what lies did you hear today?

1017
01:01:41,491 --> 01:01:43,291
Well...

1018
01:01:43,591 --> 01:01:47,431
Keep it secret
that you're the Chairman's son.

1019
01:01:48,891 --> 01:01:50,231
I asked,
"What did you two talk about?"

1020
01:01:54,131 --> 01:01:56,401
We didn't really talk
about much today.

1021
01:01:58,401 --> 01:02:01,871
I'll make sure you get
all of Taehan.

1022
01:02:09,351 --> 01:02:12,151
- Let's go. Seong Mi is waiting.
- Okay, Mom.

1023
01:02:13,151 --> 01:02:16,191
- Wrap it up. Let's go.
- Okay, go on ahead.

1024
01:02:16,691 --> 01:02:19,021
We're closed for the day.

1025
01:02:19,091 --> 01:02:20,691
(Registration and Payment)

1026
01:02:20,761 --> 01:02:22,701
Yes, this is
Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic.

1027
01:02:24,331 --> 01:02:25,761
Is this the Gong Myeong
Jeong Dae Han Clinic?

1028
01:02:26,331 --> 01:02:28,571
The one located in Onjeong?

1029
01:02:29,071 --> 01:02:31,901
Yes, it is.
This is Gong Jeong Han speaking.

1030
01:02:32,941 --> 01:02:34,071
I see.

1031
01:02:35,271 --> 01:02:38,141
I'm a fan
of the show "Human Theater."

1032
01:02:39,211 --> 01:02:41,011
Really? Is that so?

1033
01:02:42,451 --> 01:02:44,951
As I was watching
the most recent episode,

1034
01:02:45,451 --> 01:02:48,321
I couldn't shake the feeling
that your clinic looked so familiar.

1035
01:02:49,091 --> 01:02:51,721
So I called directory assistance
and asked for your number.

1036
01:02:52,191 --> 01:02:55,061
Thank you. I'm glad you enjoyed it.

1037
01:02:55,791 --> 01:02:57,101
Come on, let's go already.

1038
01:02:57,861 --> 01:03:01,901
If you ever feel sick, just stop by.
All right, take care.

1039
01:03:02,571 --> 01:03:03,701
Wait just a moment.

1040
01:03:04,801 --> 01:03:05,841
Yes?

1041
01:03:07,941 --> 01:03:09,111
By any chance,

1042
01:03:09,741 --> 01:03:11,881
do you know a man named Jo Mun Sik?

1043
01:03:13,681 --> 01:03:16,981
I don't think so.
The name doesn't ring a bell, sir.

1044
01:03:17,681 --> 01:03:19,081
I see.

1045
01:03:19,651 --> 01:03:23,121
The thing is,
I lost my memory in an accident.

1046
01:03:23,921 --> 01:03:24,921
You what?

1047
01:03:26,091 --> 01:03:29,701
So I called to ask
in case you might know who I am.

1048
01:03:31,801 --> 01:03:33,031
When did you lose...

1049
01:03:33,801 --> 01:03:34,971
I mean...

1050
01:03:35,501 --> 01:03:37,441
When did you lose your memory?

1051
01:03:37,701 --> 01:03:40,371
- Mom.
- What is it?

1052
01:03:41,271 --> 01:03:44,141
- He lost his memory? When?
- Mom, be quiet.

1053
01:03:45,111 --> 01:03:47,811
It's just been exactly 30 years.

1054
01:03:48,951 --> 01:03:50,981
Thirty years?

1055
01:03:52,521 --> 01:03:53,991
Don't tell me.

1056
01:03:54,791 --> 01:03:55,791
Sir.

1057
01:03:56,261 --> 01:03:59,061
We're actually looking for
our father right now.

1058
01:04:02,191 --> 01:04:03,231
Your father?

1059
01:04:04,261 --> 01:04:08,271
Yes, where are you right now?
I'll come over.

1060
01:04:09,101 --> 01:04:10,141
Well, I'm at...

1061
01:04:11,041 --> 01:04:14,971
- Where did he say he is?
- Sir, where are you right now?

1062
01:04:15,641 --> 01:04:17,511
Hello? Sir?

1063
01:04:18,141 --> 01:04:19,381
Hello?

1064
01:04:49,781 --> 01:04:52,781
(Recipe For Love)

1065
01:04:52,951 --> 01:04:55,581
The symbolic weight
of the founder's direct heir...

1066
01:04:55,951 --> 01:04:57,081
That's nothing to scoff at.

1067
01:04:57,151 --> 01:04:59,521
How long are you going to sit there
with that disrespectful slouch?

1068
01:04:59,651 --> 01:05:01,991
I'm entitled to sit like this.

1069
01:05:01,991 --> 01:05:04,191
Didn't you say
you might have a half-sibling?

1070
01:05:04,261 --> 01:05:07,391
Think you'll be happy to see them?
That they'll have your back?

1071
01:05:08,491 --> 01:05:11,661
I could lose everything.
I have to be careful.

1072
01:05:12,771 --> 01:05:14,131
How can I steal Seong Mi from you...

1073
01:05:14,131 --> 01:05:15,231
when you didn't even go out
with her?

1074
01:05:15,231 --> 01:05:16,401
Well...

1075
01:05:18,301 --> 01:05:19,971
It's true you were the one
who stole me.

1076
01:05:20,771 --> 01:05:23,081
Do you think she's crazy?
Why would she keep coming back here?

1077
01:05:23,311 --> 01:05:24,881
She might have her reasons
for coming to the pharmacy.

1078
01:05:25,141 --> 01:05:26,711
To see if they're on her tail.

1079
01:05:27,507 --> 01:05:29,507
Dramaday.me
